==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Covered
<hw>Cov"ered</hw> <pr>(k?v"?rd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Under cover;
screened; sheltered; not exposed; hidden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Covered way</b></col> <fld>(Fort.)</fld>, <cd>a corridor
or banquette along the top of the counterscarp and covered by an
embankment whose slope forms the glacis. It gives the garrison an open
line of communication around the works, and a standing place beyond the
ditch. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Ravelin</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coverer</ent>⟦br⟧
